  [1]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integer_overflow

For the approach you have used, using `BigInteger` like @Reilas&#39;s answer would work.

But a more simpler approach to the problem would be 
- determine if the input number plus one will result in increased number of digits in output
- declare the output array of the size accordingly
- in case of `hasCarry=true`, set `output[0]=1` and return the output (applies when input is 9, 99, etc.)
- otherwise assign the input array to the output. Increment the `output[i]` by 1 when the `input[i]&lt;9` and assign `output[i]=0` for `input[i]==9` 

```
public int[] plusOne(int[] digits) {
    boolean hasCarry = true;
    for (int digit: digits)
        if (digit != 9) {
            hasCarry = false;
            break;
        }

    int[] output = hasCarry ? new int[digits.length + 1] : new int[digits.length];

    if (hasCarry) {
        output[0] = 1;
    } else {
        output = digits;
        for (int i = output.length - 1; i &gt;= 0; i--) {
            if (digits[i] &lt; 9) {
                output[i]++;
                return output;
            }
            output[i] = 0;
        }
    }
    return output;
}
```

