Well a colleague of mine found the answer, turns out you need to tell maven where the web ressources are so i added:

           &lt;configuration&gt;
    					&lt;webResources&gt;
    							&lt;resource&gt;
    									&lt;directory&gt;$/film/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF&lt;/directory&gt;
    									&lt;targetPath&gt;WEB-INF&lt;/targetPath&gt;
    									&lt;includes&gt;
    											&lt;include&gt;**/jboss-deployment-structure.xml&lt;/include&gt;
    									 &lt;/includes&gt;
    							&lt;/resource&gt;
    					&lt;/webResources&gt;
    			&lt;/configuration&gt;


after the :

    &lt;plugin&gt;
    				&lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    				&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin
                    &lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

part of the pom  and that fixed it. Inspired by this answer: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1782352/filtering-maven-files-into-web-inf

