Note you can specify the categories of the `CategoryAxis` in code (i.e., in the controller) if you prefer.

A few other points:

* **Never** explicitly assign an `@FXML`-annotated field. For example, this:

    ```java
    @FXML
    private BarChart&lt;String,Number&gt; chart = new BarChart&lt;&gt;(xAxis, yAxis);
    ```

    Should just be:

    ```java
    @FXML
    private BarChart&lt;String, Number&gt; chart;
    ```

* All `@FXML`-annotated fields should be `private` unless you have a (rare) _good_ reason otherwise. Note any non-public field you want injected by the `FXMLLoader` must be annotated with `@FXML`.

* **Only** fields you want to be injected by the `FXMLLoader` should be annotated with `@FXML`. For example, `items` does not appear to be defined in the FXML file, so there&#39;s no reason for that field to be annotated with `@FXML`.

* [Do not use raw types][1].

    * You have two raw `ComboBox` fields.

    * All your `XYChart.Series` are raw.

    * All your `XYChart.Data` are raw.

    Parameterize all of those.





